About Asia

Asia is the central and eastern part of Eurasia, comprising approximately fifty countries. Asia is joined to Africa Link: ../africa/ by the Isthmus of Suez and to Europe Link: ../europe/ by a long border generally following the Ural Mountains Link: ../russia/ural-mountains/map.html .

The mean elevation of the continent is 950 m, the largest of any in the world. The plateau and mountainous areas broadly sweep SW-NW across Asia, climaxing in the high Tibetan Plateau, Plateau, rising to the highest peaks in the world in the Himalaya. Himalaya. To the north west lie plains, while to the south lie the geologically distinct areas of the Arabian peninsula, peninsula, Indian subcontinent and Malay peninsula. Large numbers of islands lie south east of the continent.
